Script description/

The purpose of the run_analysis script is to tidy and clean the data from the Human Recognition Samrtphone data set, to make it easy
to use for future data analysis.

The script works as follow:
1.Download the zip file from the given link
2.Merge all the test files together using cbind
3.Merge all the trazin files together usind cbind
4.Merge the resulting test and train files together using rbind in order to btain a complete data frame with all the raw data.
5.Name the columns in the resulting dataframe with the correct variables names: "subject", "activity" and the variables from the 
"feature.txt" file.
6.Crate a new data frame with only the mean and standard deviation variables (since the instruction is ambiguous, the mean 
frequency variables have been included, as it is not specified if a specific kind of mean should be selected or all of them). Identify
All columns with mean or std in their name then loop to include them in the new data frame.
7.Replace the numbers in the activity column by their description.
8.Rewrite the variables' names to make them more descriptive and therefore easier to understand.
9.Group the final data frame by activity and subject, using group_by in the dplyr package
10. Calculate the mean for each variable, for each subject by activity and store the resulting data in a tidy_data_set.txt file
